//pilates 30 MIN FULL BODY WORKOUT ,Intense home workout
Pilates is a form of holistic body exercise that emphasizes control, balance, flexibility, strength, and comprehensive respiratory training. This exercise method was originally created by German fitness trainer Joseph Pilates in the early 20th century and was initially referred to as "Contrology." It later became widely known as Pilates. Pilates focuses on developing the strength and stability of the core muscle groups, including the muscles around the torso, such as the abdomen, back, buttocks, and pelvic region. Fundamental Pilates movements highlight body symmetry, aiming to improve posture and movement efficiency through precise and fluid motions.
